@@class variable
@instance varibale
def method(local variable)
$global varialbe
CONSTANT within class or module but not under def.
puts "#{CONSTANT}"


#global variable
$country_name="India"
class Country
  #constant variable
  PLANET="earth"
  #class variable
  @@state_name="uttarakhand"
    #local variable inside method signature(name)
    def city(name)
      #instance variable
      @city_name=name
      puts "country name is #$country_name"
      puts "state name is #@@state_name"
      puts "city name is #@city_name"
    end
end
#creating object of class Country
count=Country.new
#calling method city
count.city("Dehradun")
      

note- if global variable is set with no value then it will run also with no error or warning ..
      to show warning we have to do
      ruby -w filename.rb
    

Arithmetic operator
**
a=10, b=20
then
a**b gives 10 to the power 20

Comparision operator
<=>
return 0 is equal
return -1 if operand is less
return 1 if operand is greater

.eql?
1==1.0 is true but 1.eql?(1.0) is false

equals?

===
(1..10)===5 will return true

Ruby parallel assignment
a,b,c =10,20,30


multilines comments
=begin
...
...
=end


if -else statement

if condition
elsif condition
else





